messages.content: What are the key features of Python 3.11?

Python 3.11 introduces several significant improvements: 1) Enhanced performance with up to 25% faster execution through the new interpreter optimizations. 2) Better error messages with more precise traceback information that pinpoints the exact location of errors. 3) Exception groups and the except* syntax for handling multiple exceptions. 4) Improved type annotations with the Self type and variadic generics. 5) TOML support in the standard library through tomllib.
How much faster is it compared to Python 3.10?

According to the official Python documentation, Python 3.11 is on average 25% faster than Python 3.10, with some operations showing even greater improvements. The speedup comes from several optimizations including faster startup, faster runtime through specialized adaptive interpreter, and improvements to the standard library. Benchmarks show that CPU-intensive tasks can see up to 60% performance gains in specific scenarios.
